Package edu.uw.nemo.mapreduce

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CombinerJob
    Runs a map-reduce job to collect the canonical labels to produce their total count
    CombinerMapper
    A pass through mapper which just splits the input on tab and set the canonical label as key and the other part as value
    CombinerReducer
    Collects the canonical labels and compute the aggregated count for them.
    ESUJob
    Iterative map-reduce job to enumerate sub-graphs using ESU algorithm
    EsuMapper
    Implements the extension part of the ESU algorithm with G6 format computation
    EsuReducer
    A de-duping reducer
    LabelerJob
    Runs a map-reduce job to compute canonical labels for the enumerated sub-graphs
    LabelerMapper
    Maps the g6 format string as the key so that all graphs with a particular g6 value are passed to the reducer which computes the canonical label
    LabelerReducer
    Computes the canonical label for the sub-graphs using labelg
    NemoMain
    Runs a chain of map-reduce jobs to find motifs in a biological network.
    RandomizerJob
    Runs a map-reduce job to randomize the input
    RandomizerMapper
    A randomizing mapper which randomizes the input by using a random key
    RandomizerReducer
    The reducer gets the randomized input from map tasks based on the random key used by map tasks and just outputs the values after splitting them on TAB
